Absolute diffrences kabhi (-) me value nhi aata hai ye usko posetive me change kr dega


class Solution {
public:
    int maxAdjacentDistance(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n=nums.size();
        int maxDiff=0;

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
        {
            int nextIndex=(i+1)%n;// circular behavior
            int diff=abs(nums[i]-nums[nextIndex]);// abs() ka mtlb agar negetive(-) me value aata hai to wo usko possetive me kr dega
            maxDiff= max(maxDiff, diff);
        }
        return maxDiff;
    }
};




















🔄 Circular Array Kya Hota Hai?
Circular array ek aisa array hota hai jisme last element ke baad phir se first element consider kiya jata hai.
Iska matlab: a[n−1] ke baad a[0] aata hai, jaise ki array gola (circle) ban gaya ho.

🔁 Example:
arr = [10, 20, 30, 40]
Normal adjacent pairs:

(10, 20)

(20, 30)

(30, 40)

Circular array mein ek aur pair consider hota hai:

(40, 10) ← last and first

🎯 Key Property:
Agar n size ka array hai, to:

nextIndex = (i + 1) % n
Ye trick ensure karti hai ki jab i = n-1 ho (last element), tab (n-1 + 1) % n = 0, matlab first element.

🌀 Visual Representation:
Index:      0     1     2     3
           [10] - [20] - [30] - [40]
             \__________________↑
               ←←←←←←←←←←←←←←←←←
Array gol gol chalta hai → isiliye "circular".











🔹 Definition:
👉 Adjacent Elements:
Array ke side-by-side (yaani lagatar) elements ko adjacent kaha jata hai.

For example, agar array hai:

cpp
Copy
Edit
arr = [4, 7, 2, 9]
To adjacent pairs hain:

(4, 7)

(7, 2)

(2, 9)

********************************************************************************************************************************************************
👉 Absolute Difference:
Do numbers ka absolute difference hota hai:


|a - b|
Matlab:

Agar a - b positive hai, toh wahi

Agar a - b negative hai, toh uska positive version

🔸 Absolute difference kabhi negative nahi hota

🧮 Example with Absolute Differences:
For array:

cpp
Copy
Edit
arr = [4, 7, 2, 9]
Calculate absolute differences between adjacent elements:

|4 - 7| = | -3 | = 3

|7 - 2| = | 5 | = 5

|2 - 9| = | -7 | = 7

✅ Result: [3, 5, 7]

**********************************************************************************************************************************

🔄 Circular Version:
If array is circular, then also include:

|9 - 4| = 5

Final differences: [3, 5, 7, 5]
👉 Max = 7















🧩 Given Array:
cpp
Copy
Edit
arr = [4, 7, 2, 9]
Step 1: Adjacent Pairs (Normal – Linear)
Hum side-by-side (adjacent) pairs lete hain:

Index	Pair	Calculation	Absolute Difference
0-1	4 and 7	`	4 - 7
1-2	7 and 2	`	7 - 2
2-3	2 and 9	`	2 - 9

✅ Abhi tak differences: [3, 5, 7]

Step 2: Circular Pair (Last and First)
Since yeh circular array hai, to last element (9) ko first element (4) ke sath bhi compare karna padega:

Index	Pair	Calculation	Absolute Difference
3-0	9 and 4	`	9 - 4

Now we add this to our list:
✅ Final Differences = [3, 5, 7, 5]

Step 3: Max nikalna
Now list hai: [3, 5, 7, 5]

Inme se sabse bada number kya hai?

✅ Max = 7
